# Phase 3 — Implementation plan for the audit

## Step 1: inventory the current code paths

Review and map:

* listing create endpoints
* listing update endpoints
* payment endpoints
* webhook handlers
* listing queries used on public pages
* cron / scheduled expiration logic
* admin overrides

## Step 2: define canonical listing schema

Lock down one schema for listings.

Suggested core fields:

* id
* ownerId
* ownerType
* dealerId
* createdByUserId
* status
* paymentStatus
* title
* year
* make
* model
* category
* price
* hours
* description
* location
* images
* primaryImage
* createdAt
* updatedAt
* publishedAt
* expiresAt
* soldAt
* paymentReference
* planType
* visibility

## Step 3: define canonical business rules

Examples:

* listing cannot be public if paymentStatus is not paid, unless admin override
* expiresAt must always be set when published
* sold listing cannot remain in active public results
* draft listing cannot trigger feed sync

## Step 4: write audit scripts and admin reports

Build internal tools to flag:

* listings missing expiresAt
* published listings without payment reference
* expired listings still visible
* listings with broken image URLs
* listings with duplicate payment mapping

## Step 5: write regression tests

Add automated tests around:

* publish flow
* payment webhook flow
* expiration logic
* public visibility rules

## Step 6: fix and stabilize before Meta work

Do not start dealer Meta connection until the listing pipeline is clean.

